The governments of the Netherlands nationalize part of the Fortis Bank.
The States of the Netherlands - being the first in Europe - will help with a nationalization of the Belgian-Dutch bank Fortis that is in trouble due to the effect of the mortgage crisis on the American market: the three countries will support this financial and insurance institution, which also has business in Hungary, with a total of 11.2 billion euros.
This weekend the governments of Belgium, Luxembourg and the Netherlands held higher-level consultations with the President of the European Central Bank and the European Commission's economic competition.
The Fortis Bank is the first to suffer the crisis in the euro area in the context of the international financial crisis that is taking place in several waves more than a year ago, so the decisions taken with respect to the Bank, in a sense, can be seen as precedents.
According to the decision taken in the morning of Sunday, the three states will buy about half (49%) of the property owned by the Bank in their area.
The Bank will certainly sell a part of its business, including mainly the activities - mainly insurance - purchased last year from the Dutch ABN Amró.
The actions of the Fortis began a sharp decline last week and by the second half of the week there were already important signs of crisis in the institution.
However, analysts agree to point out that with its 85 thousand employees this Bank is too big to allow it to break.
The company's shares fell by 12 percent on Friday alone, with this being the lowest point in the last 14 years.
Since January the value of the shares has been reduced by more than two thirds.
Noting the current stock prices, the total value of the group's capital on the market is about 14 billion euros, but according to the company's executives this is not real.
The Bank's management attributed the sharp fall in the shares of Fortis to the insecurities of the American market in relation to the approval of the US $700 billion package plan.
On Monday the actions already showed a slight increase.
On Friday, Filip Dierckx was appointed as the new general director of the bank.
The Bank also sought private investors, but so far no one has given a specific offer.
The Belgian government had previously assured that investors did not have to worry, they will not lose their money.
There was no panic among the Bank's clients so far, they did not invade the bank offices to withdraw their money.
Fortis has its own branch in Hungary and has also bought leasing companies.
Fox in the hens
In the United States, life and health insurance companies are often denied to sign an insurance contract when they see the data from the purchase of medicine.
Privacy policy specialists fear that the personal data market will become uncontrollable.
"There are programmes for the protection of personal data, which, when using the data of the recipes in all cases, binds it to the approval of the given person.
The same must be in independent hands, because if not, "we trust the hens to the fox" - quotes the Washington Post to Richard Dick, designer of the program to follow up medical recipes.
Insurance companies make the insurance price and the amount of compensation for the customer's state of health dependent and if they believe that the risk is excessive, they simply do not make the contract.
They previously sent the client to medical control and signed the contract with him, already knowing the result of the control.
Dick invented a much cheaper procedure ten years ago: with the customer's identification number he easily gets from pharmacies the list of medicines bought in the last year and a half and the program itself draws the conclusion about the customer's diseases and state of health.
For example, if you systematically take large doses of cholesterol reduction pills, it indicates that the fat level in the blood is almost incurably high, so it is immediately included in a higher risk category.
There are many versions of the program, some even set a risk number, so the insurance company in addition to the administration has little to do, although there are small difficulties in this respect.
Among the disadvantages of the program is, for example, that some medicines are multi-use, for example, certain substances are used to treat both headache and heat waves and even antidepressants.
The latter is an important risk-raising factor for insurance companies while the former are not.
Special companies were set up to consult and process these data, which before acquiring the necessary information from pharmacies, call for the patient's approval.
The authorities already force them to do this, although they did not receive a fine for the negligence of so far.
Some companies have recently also produced the results of the laboratory tests and, together with the drug use data, obtain more accurate information on the patient's health status.
More and more companies have access to these data and simultaneously it is increasingly difficult to control their use.
There is an exclusive law for the protection of personal health data, but it applies only to insurance companies and those providing health services.
The bill that provides the authority for the control of specialized companies for the provision of personal data is already before Congress.
Dick Richard recognizes that this is insufficient: he therefore developed his program, which will require the specific approval of the person for the provision of his own personal data.
It is another issue that the person cannot deny his approval, because if the insurance companies do not sign the contract with him.
So the hens, however, are exposed to the good will of the fox.
