The Commissioner has specified that no human remains have been found either on the plane or in the surroundings.
The millionaire, 63 years old, has been considered dead in February.
The American transport safety office (Ntsb) has informed that a few hours after the sighting of the remains, a squadron of researchers has been sent that has identified the apparatus: it is typical of the Bellanca 8kcab, scattered since September 3, 2007, when Fossett took off from Yerington in Nevada for a three-hour flight.
Yesterday, always in California, not far from the Nevada border, some personal remains of Fossett have been found by a couple near their home in Mammoth Lakes.
These are two documents with the name Fossett, the two issued by the Illinois Federal Aviation Administration, cash and a sweatshirt.
The search for Fossett had been interrupted one month after his disappearance.
